    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-osel-vv40-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment package for COU1 is accepted at Medium assurance level. Ten of thirteen V&V 40 factors are fully assessed and meet or exceed required gradation levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3, representing a documented shortfall consistent with the single-condition F1717 protocol; this gap is judged acceptable given corroborating inter-laboratory consistency. Two factors (Numerical solver error and Use error) remain not-assessed, with rationale citing scope limitations; this is considered acceptable by the assessment team given the quasi-static linear regime and analyst experience, though it is noted that at modelRiskLevel 3 these unassessed factors represent a residual epistemic gap that has not been formally bounded.",
